$29.00 with tip, 9 jerk wings app, burger with dry salad (I chose salad instead of fries). The wings were some of the best I've ever had, I wish they'd put a 1/4 or 1/2 jerk chicken on the menu instead of the very ordinary crab cakes, burger, shrimp, blah, blah... The burger was fair, but nothing special. My waiter asked what kind of dressing on my salad, I agreed to his suggestion (balsamic vinaigrette), and it showed up without dressing. Everyone was so kind and wonderful, two different staff members asked my opinion about how to place jerk chicken on the menu, but the sound level is geared for a bar, not a conversation. I could hardly communicate in any meaningful way what came up short. So.... Five stars for the appetizer, five for the friendly staff, two stars for the noisy room that made communication a challenge, two stars for the ok burger, one star for the pile of lettuce with no dressing. I'll go back and see if they make the menu more robust, I'd like to eat a lot more of their Jerk, damn good stuff.

I really like this place BUT I’m surprised that an automatic gratuity was added to my check without my knowledge. But I was disappointed to learn that an $8.00 tip was added to my $36.00 check during happy hour! Plus I was sitting at the bar with my partner, it was only two of us. This is the second time I came to treehouse within the last couple of weeks. The first time it was great! Andre made us feel so comfortable AND he didn’t add a gratuity to the check maybe because his service is great and he doesn’t have to. Needless to say the service tonight was below par, the bartenders were busy entertaining one of their regulars and ignored the rest of us, which is why I assume they added the gratuity. #notok
